 new ones are reborn. In each such =\r\nworld there will be a Hanumana, a Rama and a Rama&#39;s ring.&quot;\n\n\n-Regards\n=C2=\r\n=A0Rajarshi\n\n\nawaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |\nparam bhAwama=\r\njAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]\n\n\n________________________________\n Fr=\r\nom: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt;\nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \nS=\r\nent: Monday, 30 July 2012 8:16 AM\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: To those who =\r\nsay that they don=E2=80=99t believe in any religion\n \n\n=C2=A0 \nDear Rajarsh=\r\ni,\n=C2=A0\n&lt;&lt;I do not believe in Moksha. What is Moksha? No rebirth? If the =\r\nUniverse itself gets born over and over and over, if Rama and Krshna come b=\r\nack at every cycle, who am I to demand that I should not get born?&gt;&gt;\n=C2=A0=\r\n\nWhen we are talking about god, moksha and self-realization, what we unders=\r\ntand of those words/concepts is influenced by our conditioning. As our cond=\r\nitioning becomes lighter, our understanding gets refined.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nOne person who values power may see god as one with this power=\r\n and that power. One person who values love and kindness may see god as one=\r\n who is loving and kind to all. One person who values freedom may see god a=\r\ns one who is completely free. One person who values knowledge may see god a=\r\ns one who knows everything. And so on. Though all these may be true to some=\r\n extent, none of them capture the concept of god well.\n=C2=A0\nOne person wi=\r\nth fear or distaste for rebirth may think that moksha is freedom from rebir=\r\nth. One person with distaste for action may think that moksha is freedom fr=\r\nom action. One person who is fascinated by happiness may think that moksha =\r\nis supreme happiness. And so on. Though all these may be true to some exten=\r\nt, none of them capture the concept of moksha well.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=