uot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div ali=\r\ngn=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;I will tell=\r\n you how I see it. In this story, God means infinity. Now what is infinity?=\r\n It cannot be described, it cannot be named, it cannot be understood using =\r\nthe five sense organs. Science does not understand infinity, art\n does not =\r\nunderstand infinity, nothing or nobody&nbsp; understands infinity. It is a =\r\nsummation of all that we know, all that we can&nbsp; imagine and all that i=\r\ns impossible for us to imagine. It is an incomprehensible force that runs t=\r\nhrough everything, from the most loveable to the most despicable , from the=\r\n most holy to the most unholy, from the greatest saint to the stupidest pie=\r\nce of rock at the bottom of the deepest ocean in the farthest planet in the=\r\n farthest solar system in the farthest universe. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=3D=\r\n&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D=\r\n&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; fa=\r\nce=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#00=\r\n0000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Now question is, can an average human being &quot;know&quot; t=\r\nhis mysterious and all pervading force? Knowing implies understanding. Clea=\r\nrly no. Then how does one interact with such a thing? One way is to conside=\r\nr\n everything, and I mean EVERYTHING from living to non-living, as a manife=\r\nstation of that force and thus learn to love the same unconditionally witho=\r\nut expecting anything in return. No wonder such unconditional love is not e=\r\nasy. It needs tremendous effort to change our own conditioning of the mind,=\r\n and work on our inherent biases and prejudices. That is what the&nbsp; aim=\r\n of sadhana is, in my view. To work on oneself, to make one ready to be abl=\r\ne to unconditionally love everything. The greater number of entities one ca=\r\nn love unconditionally, that much little bit closer one can come to interac=\r\nting with the truly infinite. And those few rare human beings who can love =\r\na whole universe unconditionally, are possibly the closest to this supreme =\r\nand unknowable force. In common language, we call them Rishis. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div=\r\n&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;I like all fo=\r\nrms of\n Deities, for I find something beautiful in everyone of them. And I =\r\nalso like the One behind forms, which is so perfectly transcendental that i=\r\nt cannot be comprehended ever. It&#39;s like the surface area of the fine tip o=\r\nf a needle, or the gap between the two breaths, or the millionth part of a =\r\nsingle hair, or the endless-ness of space, or the bottomless well of stilln=\r\ness in the mind at certain points in meditation. The only thing that stops =\r\nme from getting a better understanding the grandeur of&nbsp; this formless =\r\nentity are the limitations of my own mind and body, that I have acquired ov=\r\ner millions of births. That is why Sadhana. To slowly gnaw away at my own m=\r\nind, to be better able to appreciate this endless, nameless entity. G_d. &lt;f=\r\nont size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=\r\n=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;=\r\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;=\r\nVerdana&quot;&gt;I do not\n believe in Moksha. What is Moksha? No rebirth? If the Un=\r\niverse itself gets born over and over and over, if Rama and Krshna come bac=\r\nk at every cycle, who am I to demand that I should not get born? Infact, wh=\r\nen a person proverbially finishes off his/her karmas, they merely go to ano=\r\nther plane in this Universe and stay there for eons of time, since time any=\r\nway moves very, very slowly in different realms. But then, if this force so=\r\n wants, it can send back any of the souls from any of the realms to any of =\r\nthe other realms to serve a certain function. And if a soul stays in a cert=\r\nain higher realm and in forced to take rebirth again, the seeds of the karm=\r\nas - which never really die off - are&nbsp; watered again by the environmen=\r\nt of birth and they sprout into saplings. And this may go even beyond one c=\r\nycle of creation. Else why would Krshna and Arjuna fight the very same enem=\r\nies that they had been fighting in the past cycle of creation? Mahabharata =\r\nsays so. I\n believe it. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; fac=\r\ne=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana=\r\n&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font=\r\n&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;3&quot; color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Wh=\r\nat then is the final aim of all this, spirituality etc? I don&#39;t know. Maybe=\r\n, to teach us to broaden our perspectives and consequentially lessen our at=\r\ntachments to our otherwise mundane lives and its mundane problems. This is =\r\nlike a circular roller-coaster ride we see in local melas. Tighten the seat=\r\n-belts, bring a smile in the heart, be detached and e